<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="170" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,151,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Shimbori &amp; Bortoni &amp; Shaw &amp; Souza-Gessner &amp; Cerântola &amp; Penteado-Dias, 2019" authorityName="Shimbori &amp; Bortoni &amp; Shaw &amp; Souza-Gessner &amp; Cerântola &amp; Penteado-Dias" authorityYear="2019" box="[327,574,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Adelius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ecuadoriensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[327,574,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Adelius ecuadoriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[580,643,151,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[580,643,151,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is completely black, with infuscate wings and brown veins and stigma. The fore wing cross vein r is present, and hind coxa is rugose dorsally. It closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Shimbori &amp; Bortoni &amp; Shaw &amp; Souza-Gessner &amp; Cerântola &amp; Penteado-Dias, 2019" authorityName="Shimbori &amp; Bortoni &amp; Shaw &amp; Souza-Gessner &amp; Cerântola &amp; Penteado-Dias" authorityYear="2019" box="[1188,1313,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Adelius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excelsus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1188,1313,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">A. excelsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1321,1385,188,213]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1321,1377,188,213]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">sp. n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
The distinction between these species is made under diagnosis for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shimbori &amp; Bortoni &amp; Shaw &amp; Souza-Gessner &amp; Cerântola &amp; Penteado-Dias" authorityYear="2019" box="[845,969,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Adelius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excelsus">
<emphasis box="[845,969,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">A. excelsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,287,260,285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Biology</emphasis>
. Unknown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,295,320]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Distribution</emphasis>
. Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[608,656,296,320]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">type</typeStatus>
locality. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,332,357]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Etymology</emphasis>
. This species is named after 
<collectingCountry box="[650,745,332,357]" name="Ecuador" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, the country where it was discovered.
</paragraph>
